# CULTIVATION SIMULATOR — ONBOARDING ARC IMPLEMENTATION TASK LIST
### Progressive UI Disclosure System
### All tasks are self-contained and independently implementable

---

## DESIGN OVERVIEW

The onboarding system is built on three independent layers that can be developed in parallel:

**Layer 1 — UIVisibility:** A registry that knows which UI elements exist and which are currently shown. Every element in the game starts hidden. The registry decides what to reveal and when.

**Layer 2 — OnboardingState:** A state machine tracking which chapter the player is in, which tutorial steps are complete, and what condition triggers the next step. Completely decoupled from rendering.

**Layer 3 — TutorialOverlay:** The visual presentation layer — spotlights, tooltip cards, animated arrows, chapter transition screens. Consumes OnboardingState and UIVisibility, produces what the player sees.

All three layers operate against a **GameStateView** — a read-only interface that the real simulation will satisfy but that can be mocked immediately for testing and development.

